unittitle.value: Kenneth Silverman Research Collection on Samuel F.B. Morse

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value:
This collection contains research materials collected by Kenneth Silverman while working on his book 
                <title render="italic">Lightning Man: The Accursed Life of Samuel F.B. Morse.</title> Materials include photocopied articles and essays, microfilm, and correspondence (mostly transcribed) dating from 1792 to 1892. This collection does not include original materials from Morse.

p.value:
Open for research without restrictions. This collection is in
                <extref ns2:href="http://www.nyu.edu/library/bobst/research/arch/morseresearch.htm">
                    <archref> off-site storage</archref> </extref>.

Published citations should take the following form: Identification of item, date (if known); Kenneth Silverman Research Collection on Samuel F.B. Morse; MC 173; box number; folder number; New York University Archives, New York University Libraries.

<list>
                    <item>All biographic information about Kenneth Silverman from the NYU website.</item>
                    <item>Dim, Joan Marans, and Nancy Murphy Cricco. 
                        <title render="italic">The Miracle on Washington Square: New York University. </title> Lanham: Lexington, 2001.</item>
                </list>

This collection includes photocopied articles and essays, microfilm, correspondence (mostly transcribed) and other research materials. The dates range from 1792-1892. The folders in the collection are arranged chronologically and by subject.
